Package com.ikanow.aleph2.data_model.objects.data_import

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AnnotationBean
    A generic "underlay" for document-like data objects Can be inserted into a JSON object as the field "__a" and provides a lightweight mechanism for application-aware tagging ALL FIELDS ARE OPTIONAL - NO PART OF THE CORE WILL ASSUME ANY OF THEM EXIST
    AnnotationBean.AssociationBean
    Encapsulates the concept that "entities" in documents can be explicity associated more strongly than simply by co-reference
    AnnotationBean.EntityBean
    Encapsulates the concept of an "entity" in a document: a person, a place, an abstract concept
    AnnotationBean.GeoTemporalBean
    Encapsulates a geo-temporal associations within the document
    AnnotationBean.MentionBean  
    BucketDiffBean
    Placeholder object for representing the differences in a bucket update, to help harvest/enrichment authors decide how best to handle them
    DataBucketBean
    A very important bean that describes how a bucket gets and stores its data
    DataBucketBean.Template
    Encapsulates a template object used to create this bucket Ie the information in the list of templates (ids + subs) is sufficient to recreate an identical bucket
    DataBucketStatusBean
    Represents generic harvest status
    DataSchemaBean
    Immutable object describing the data from this bucket
    DataSchemaBean.ColumnarSchemaBean
    Per bucket schema for the Columnar Service
    DataSchemaBean.DataWarehouseSchemaBean
    Per bucket schema for the Data Warehouse service
    DataSchemaBean.DocumentSchemaBean
    Per bucket schema for the Document Service
    DataSchemaBean.GeospatialSchemaBean
    Per bucket schema for the Geospatial Service
    DataSchemaBean.GraphSchemaBean
    Per bucket schema for the Graph DB Service
    DataSchemaBean.SearchIndexSchemaBean
    Per bucket schema for the Search Index Service
    DataSchemaBean.StorageSchemaBean
    Per bucket schema for the Archive Service
    DataSchemaBean.StorageSchemaBean.StorageSubSchemaBean
    Covers the generic storage parameters for each of the raw/json/processed cases
    DataSchemaBean.TemporalSchemaBean
    Per bucket schema for the Temporal Service
    DataSchemaBean.WriteSettings
    A class shared across multiple schema (currently: search_index_schema) that contains somewhat generic write options
    EnrichmentControlMetadataBean
    Bean controlling an enrichment configuration
    HarvestControlMetadataBean
    Bean controlling a harvester configuration - normally found embedded within a DataBucketBean
